		<field id="1" group="1" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">A During this decade, there was an overall upward trend in the percentage who were mainly informed by television.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="2" group="2" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">B In 1989 there was a noticeable drop in the figure for television.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="3" group="3" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="false">C In 1992 the percentage for those who were informed by television was seven times higher than for those who relied on radio.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="4" group="4" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="false">D In 1997 the percentage who were informed by newspapers was just over twice the percentage for radio.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="5" group="5" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="false">E The figure for those who were informed by radio in 1989 was the same as for newspapers in 1998.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="6" group="6" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">F The percentage for those who mainly relied on radio or newspapers for world news declined over the period.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="7" group="7" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="false">G The percentage for those who relied on newspapers rose slightly in 1991, 1993, 1995,1996 and 1997.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="8" group="8" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">H The smallest proportion of the population were informed by radio.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="9" group="9" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="false">I There was a 1 per cent rise in the percentage who were informed by television in 1992.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="10" group="10" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">J There was a more marked decline for newspapers than for radio.</answer>
		</field>
		<field id="11" group="11" type="i:target" mode="0">
			<answer correct="true">K Throughout this period most people received their news about the world from television.</answer>
		</field>
